feat. [[Big in Japan (band)|Big In Japan]])\n* 2011 - [[Chimes & Bells]] \u2013 The Mole\n* 2011 - [[Chimes & Bells]] \u2013 This Far\n* 2011 - Trentem\u00f8ller \u2013 Shades Of Marble\n* 2011 - [[Efterklang]] \u2013 Raincoats\n* 2011 - [[The D\u00f8]] \u2013 Too Insistent\n* 2011 - Giana Factory \u2013 Dirty Snow\n* 2011 - [[Sleep Party People]] \u2013 The Dwarf And The Horse\n* 2011 - Darkness Falls \u2013 The Void\n* 2011 - Darkness Falls \u2013 Timeline\n* 2011 - Trentem\u00f8ller \u2013 Neverglade\n* 2011 - [[Bruce Springsteen]] \u2014 State Trooper (Unofficial)\n* 2011 - [[I Got You On Tape]] \u2013 Springsteen\n* 2011 - [[Dorit Chrysler]] \u2013 Come On Home\n* 2011 - [[M83 (band)|M83]] \u2013 Midnight City\n* 2012 - [[The Drums]] \u2013 Days\n* 2012 - [[Lower Dens]] \u2014 Brains\n* 2012 - Medina \u2013 Forever\n* 2012 - [[Mikael Simpson]] \u2013 Lad Det Staa\n* 2012 - [[David Lynch]] \u2013 Pinky\u2019s Dream\n* 2013 - Howl Baby Howl \u2014 That Good Night\n* 2013 - [[The Warlocks]] \u2014 Shake The Dope Out\n* 2013 - [[Jakob Bro]] \u2014 Terrace Place\n* 2014 - [[Reptile Youth]] \u2013 JJ\n* 2014 - [[Jenny Wilson (singer)|Jenny Wilson]] \u2013 Pyramids (Rose Out of Our Pain)\n* 2014 - [[I Blame Coco|Eliot Sumner]] - Information\n* 2014 - Fraser Mcguinness - The Sun Moves On\n* 2014 - [[Future 3]] feat. [[Benoit Pioulard]] - Revenant\n* 2014 - RA - Prism\n* 2014 - Trentem\u00f8ller \u2014 River Of Life\n* 2014 - Trentem\u00f8ller \u2014 Come Undone\n* 2014 - Trentem\u00f8ller \u2014 Deceive\n* 2014 - [[Mames Babegenush]] - A Woman (feat. Reculture)\n* 2016 - [[The Soft Moon]] - Black\n* 2016 - [[Kira Skov]] - I Celebrate My Life\n* 2016 - [[Jennylee]] - Boom Boom\n* 2016 - Trentem\u00f8ller \u2014 River In Me\n* 2016 - [[Savages (band)|Savages]] - Surrender\n* 2017 - [[UNKLE]] \u2014 Looking for the Rain\n* 2017 - [[TOYDRUM]] feat. Joel Wells - Void & Form\n* 2017 - Trentem\u00f8ller \u2014 One Eye Open\n* 2017 - Trentem\u00f8ller \u2014 Hands Down\n* 2018 - [[A Place To Bury Strangers]] \u2014 Never Coming Back\n* 2020 - School of X \u2014 Write My Name\n* 2020 - 2nd Blood \u2014 Turn It Back\n* 2020 - Blaue Blume \u2014 Lovable\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Awards and nominations===\nTrentem\u00f8ller has received two [[Danish Music Award]]s for his 2006 debut album ''[[The Last Resort (album)|The Last Resort]]'', in the categories \"Danish Electronica Release of the Year\" and \"Danish Producer of the Year\", in 2007. He was first awarded a [[Danish DeeJay Awards|Danish DeeJay Award]] in 2004 for his [[Extended play|EP]] ''Trentem\u00f8ller EP'', and have since received a total of 11 awards. In 2010 Trentem\u00f8ller was nominated \"Best Remixed Recording, Non-Classical\" at the [[52nd Grammy Awards]] for his remix of [[Franz Ferdinand (band)|Franz Ferdinand]]'s \"[[No You Girls]]\".\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n!Year\n!Award\n!Category\n!Nominated work\n!Result\n|-\n||2004\n|rowspan=\"11\"|[[Danish DeeJay Awards|Danish DeeJay Award]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ddja.dk/|title=Danish DeeJay Awards|website=Danish DeeJay Awards 2018|accessdate=19 April 2018}}</ref>\n|Danish Up Front Release of the Year\n|''Trentem\u00f8ller EP''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n||2005\n|Danish Producer of the Year\n|\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|2006\n|Danish Artist of the Year\n|\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|Danish Remix of the Year\n|[[R\u00f6yksopp]] - \"[[What Else Is There?]]\" <small>(Trentem\u00f8ller Remix)</small>\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Danish DeeJay Favourite of the Year\n|\"Rykketid\"\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Danish Producer of the Year\n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Danish Up Front Release of the Year\n|\"Rykketid\"\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"11\"|2007\n|Danish Artist of the Year\n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Danish Album of the Year\n|''[[The Last Resort (album)|The Last Resort]]''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Danish Remix of the Year\n|[[Moby]] - [[Go (Moby song)|Go!]] <small>(Trentem\u00f8ller Remix)</small>\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Danish Producer of the Year\n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Danish Music Awards|Danish Music Award]]<ref>[http://ifpi.dk/dma/index.php?pk_menu=27]{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n|Danish New Act of the Year\n|\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|Danish Electronica Release of the Year\n|rowspan=\"3\"|''The Last Resort''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Danish Producer of the Year\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|Steppeulv<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaffa.dk/nyhed/8593|title=Steppeulv-nomineringer offentliggjort|last=Oppenl\u00e6nder|first=Anne-Sofie|date=8 December 2006|publisher=[[Gaffa (magazine)|Gaffa]]|language=Danish|accessdate=22 February 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaffa.dk/nyhed/9040|title=Reportage: Steppeulven 2007|last=Nielsen|first=Mathias|date=3 February 2007|publisher=[[Gaffa (magazine)|Gaffa]]|language=Danish|accessdate=22 February 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gaffa.dk/artikel/12454|title=Steppeulven 2008 er uddelt|last=St\u00e6hr|first=Maria Therese Seefeldt|date=2 February 2008|publisher=[[Gaffa (magazine)|Gaffa]]|language=Danish|accessdate=22 February 2010}}</ref>\n|Album of the Year\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|Musician of the Year\n|\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|Composer of the Year\n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Producer of the Year\n|\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"8\"|2008\n|Live Act of the Year\n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Beatport Music Awards|Beatport Music Award]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beatportal.com/feed/item/beatport-music-awards-nominees|title=Beatport: DJ & Dance Music, Tracks & Mixes|website=Beatportal.com|accessdate=19 April 2018}}</ref>\n|Best Chillout Artist\n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Best Electronica Artist\n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Best Minimal Artist\n|\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|Best Tech House Artist\n|\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Danish DeeJay Award\n|Danish Artist of the Year\n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Danish DeeJay Favourite of the Year\n|rowspan=\"2\"|\"Moan\" (feat. [[Ane Trolle]])\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|Danish Up Front Release of the Year\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2010\n|P3 Guld<ref>{{cite 